▪ Run container centos or ubuntu in an interactive
mode 
▪ Run the following command in the container
“echo docker
▪ Open a bash shell in the container and touch a
file named hello-docker 

[rshdan@localhost ~]$ docker container run -it ubuntu 
Unable to find image 'ubuntu:latest' locally
latest: Pulling from library/ubuntu
2726e237d1a3: Pull complete 
Digest: sha256:1e622c5f073b4f6bfad6632f2616c7f59ef256e96fe78bf6a595d1dc4376ac02
Status: Downloaded newer image for ubuntu:latest
root@3b019d447b34:/# echo "docker"
docker
root@3b019d447b34:/# bash
root@3b019d447b34:/# touch hello-docker



▪ Stop the container and remove it. Write your 

comment about the file hello-docker
[rshdan@localhost ~]$ docker container stop 3b019d447b34 
3b019d447b34
[rshdan@localhost ~]$ docker container rm 3b019d447b34 
3b019d447b34
[rshdan@localhost ~]$ 

#comment file will be removed 




▪ Remove all stopped containers
[rshdan@localhost ~]$ docker container prune 
WARNING! This will remove all stopped containers.
Are you sure you want to continue? [y/N] y
Total reclaimed space: 0B
[rshdan@localhost ~]$ 








